  "text": "Kumar et al, [CITATION_1] attempted the semiquantitative grading of lymphocytic infiltration in auto-immune thyroiditis. These authors used a 2 tier grading system of 1) minimal and 2) moderate to heavy lymphocytic infiltration. In their series of 55 cases, 61.9%of the cases exhibited minimal and 38.1% had moderate to heavy lymphocytic infiltration. They found a statistically significant correlation between lymphocytic infiltration and the hormonal status of the patients (p=0.02). In the present study grading of lymphocytic thyroiditis on cytology correlated well with clinical, biochemical and ultrasonographic parameters which may be attributed to relatively large sample size.",
